The reproducer involves a commutative intrinsic (`llvm.smin`). `isIdenticalToWhenDefined` handles commutativity. However, it seems to be failing to also check for attribute equality *in the commutative case*.

The original bug report mentions `combineIRFlags` failing. This function is called when CSEing two instructions. It tries to merge their fast-math flags and other attributes. The assertion means it was asked to merge incompatible attributes (like `strictfp` and no-`strictfp`) because `isEqual` wrongly said the instructions were identical.

